Date: 26/2/1965
Source: Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: <i>Second cut</i>: (i) A blow made to remove wool which has not been cut close enough to the skin; (ii) Short wool which has been produced by second cutting.
Notes: (H.A.L.Laing)

Date: 21/2/1968
Source: Straight Furrow
Author:
Vol / Page: 20
Edition:
Quote: SECOND CUT: (i) A blow made to remove wool that has been left too long in shearing. (ii) Short wool that had been cut in a `second cut'.
Notes:

Date: 24/2/1977
Source: Dominion
Author:
Vol / Page: 11
Edition:
Quote: <i>Second cut</i> (1) A blow made to remove wool that has been left too long in shearing. (2) Short wool that was cut in a `second cut'
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1982
Source: MAF Agricultural Glossary
Author:
Vol / Page: 58
Edition:
Quote: <i>Second cut:</i> Wool which is cut twice during shearing when the first cut is above the base of the staple. These short pieces of wool are of little value.
